  "prompt": "What came before the multiverse?",
  "response": "The concept of what existed \"before\" the multiverse is a complex philosophical and theoretical question without a definitive scientific answer. Different theories propose various possibilities:\n\n1. Scientific perspectives:\n- Some theories suggest there was a pre-existing quantum state or quantum vacuum\n- Eternal inflation models propose continuous universe generation\n- Some theoretical physicists argue the concept of \"before\" may not be meaningful at that scale\n\n2. Philosophical perspectives:\n- Some argue that \"before\" is an inapplicable concept outside our known spacetime\n- Metaphysical explanations might include a primordial state of pure potential\n- Religious or cosmological views offer various creation narratives\n\n3. Theoretical physics proposals:\n- String theory suggests potential \"branes\" or dimensional layers\n- Quantum mechanics indicates potential for multiple simultaneous states\n- Some models propose cyclical universe scenarios\n\nHowever, these are primarily speculative ideas. Currently, there's no conclusive scientific consensus about what, if anything, preceded the multiverse. The nature of existence before our current understanding of cosmic origins remains an open question at the boundaries of human knowledge.\n\nThe honest scientific response is: We don't know with certainty.",
